      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No worries, I'm glad I could sneak in a bit of goblin humor. Now, about security: it's a bit of a tricky situation, but don't worry, I've got the lowdown. In most cases, you won't need to go through security again for the transfer. You'll typically be allowed to proceed to the gate without re-clearing security, as long as you're already cleared for your initial flight and you're not changing airlines.\n\nHowever, it's always best to check with your airline or the airport's website to confirm their specific procedures for connecting flights. Some airports, like LHR, have dedicated connecting areas or \"jetways\" that allow passengers to move quickly between gates, while others might require you to re-clear security or use a separate security checkpoint.\n\nJust be aware that if you're transferring to a different airline, you might need to go through security again, even if it's just a quick re-clear. But for a domestic or international transfer, like your JFK to SIN flight, you should be able to breeze through without any issues. Just keep an eye on the signs and announcements, and follow the crowd of fellow travelers who are trying to make their connections on time.",
